JOHANNESBURG - Five times Grammy Award winners Ladysmith Black Mbazo has joined in on the Africa month celebrations. The legendary isicathamiya group will be performing at the Baseline Festival in Newtown on Saturday. Established in 1960 by Joseph Shabalala, the all male choral group rose to prominence with their 1986 album Graceland - featuring Paul Simon. The group was in eNCA's studio on Saturday morning to give us a sneak preview of their performance. Watch the video above. eNCA